COMPUTER TIME s.r.l
===================
Progetto: Aron Web Manager
Anno: Maggio 2015
Tony P. <antonio@ctime.it>

INSTALL STEP-BY-STEP
====================

- As Root Server:

 0- # Installazione Debian 8.1
 1- # aptitude install  squid3 \
                        dansguardian \
                        python-mysqldb \
                        python-django \
                        python-pip \
                        exim4-daemon-heavy \
                        dovecot-mysql \
                        firehol \
                        mysql-server \
                        clamav-daemon \
                        git \
                        apache2 \
                        libapache2-mod-wsgi \
                        isc-dhcp-server \
                        libsodium-dev \
                        sudo \
                        hdparm \
			            python-crypto \
			            python-bcrypt

 2- # pip install singlemodeladmin
 3- # pip install django-sizefield
 4- # pip install libnacl
 5- # pip install base58
 6- # cd /usr/local/src/
 7- # git clone https://github.com/darklow/django-suit
 8- # cd django-suit
 9- # python setup.py install
10- # touch /etc/squid3/mac_allow /etc/squid3/classes_allow
11- # chmod 666 /etc/squid3/squid.conf
12- # chmod 666 /etc/firehol/mac_allow
14- # chmod 666 /etc/network/interfaces
15- # chmod 666 /var/log/squid3/cache.log
16- # chmod 666 /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf
17- # echo "www-data ALL=(ALL:ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL" >> /etc/sudoers


- Cloning product

$ cd /usr/local/src
$ git clone http://aron.ctimeapps.it/tony/aron-web.git
$ cd aron-web

- Enter into MySQL Server with the administrator pass setup into install packages

1- $ mysql -u root -h localhost -p
2- mysql> create database aron;
3- mysql> grant all privileges on aron.* to 'aron'@'localhost' identified by 'Password0fFantasy';
4- mysql> flush privileges;
5- mysql> exit;
6- $ mysql -u root -h localhost -p aron < schema/init.sql


- Edit settings.py in order to set user / pass / database / files / uid / gid settings.

# vim web/settings.py


- Aron Manager

# python manage.py migrate
# python manage.py loaddata schema/data.json

- VirtualHost

# vim /etc/apache2/site-available/aron.conf

<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName debian.ctimeapps.it
    ServerAlias *.ctimeapps.it
    WSGIScriptAlias / /usr/local/src/aron-web/web/wsgi.py
    Alias /static/ /usr/local/src/aron-web/static/
    <Directory />
        Require all granted
    </Directory>
    <Location "/static/">
        Options -Indexes
    </Location>
</VirtualHost>

# a2ensite aron.conf
# /etc/init.d/apache2 restart
